Despite negative media reports about the governorship election, being held in Ekiti State, there was calm and peace all over the state. According to INDEPENDENT reports, even miscreants were not molested, but were controlled by the security agents on the ground. However, there were pockets of challenges and incidents. At Ward 001, Unit 01 in Udi area of Ado Ekiti, an unidentified party agent poured acid on another party agent, who is also yet to be identified. The victim was immediately treated with some native balm and palm oil. At Ward 9 Oye Ekiti, the card readers could not reflect thumbprints and the Independent National Election Commission, INEC, staff are trying rectify the situation as at the time of filing this report. Also, at Ward 6, Unit 9 Oye Ekiti, non-indigene students of Federal University of Oye, who tried to vote, were being resisted by the residents or the town and the INEC staffs were also trying to resolve the issue. At Igede Ward 2, Unit 15, there were some challenges with the card readers. Early in the morning at the Aramoko, INEC centre, there was confusion, as the security agents, were confused as to where they are posted. Dr Kayode Fayemi and his wife arrived at their Ward 11, Unit 9 polling unit by 10.15am and the former governor voted exactly 10.23am. However, his wife, Erelu Bisi Fayemi, had issues with the card reader, that rejected her thumbprint. She was advised to return to the polling booth later in the day for it to be resolved.   comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE. 